  "prompt": "How do you know if a guy is obsessed with you?",
  "response": "Recognizing if a guy is obsessed with you can involve observing a combination of behaviors and patterns. Here are some signs that might indicate obsession:\n\n1. **Constant Communication**: He frequently texts, calls, or messages you, often expecting immediate responses. \n\n2. **Tracking Your Activities**: He pays close attention to your whereabouts or activities, sometimes even showing up unexpectedly.\n\n3. **Excessive Compliments**: He makes grand declarations of affection or admiration, sometimes to an uncomfortable degree.\n\n4. **Jealousy**: He displays jealousy or possessiveness when you interact with other guys, often questioning you about them.\n\n5. **Over-Frequenting**: He tries to spend as much time as possible with you, often prioritizing his schedule around yours.\n\n6. **Lack of Boundaries**: He disregards your personal space and boundaries, pushing to learn more about you than you\u2019re comfortable sharing.\n\n7. **Invasive Questions**: He asks very personal questions early on and may pressure you to disclose more about your life.\n\n8. **Social Media Surveillance**: He closely follows your social media, liking and commenting on almost everything you post.\n\n9. **Manipulative Behavior**: He may use guilt or emotional pressure to keep you close or make you feel responsible for his feelings.\n\n10. **Neglect of Other Relationships**: He may neglect his friendships or family to be with you, often isolating himself.\n\nWhile some of these behaviors can indicate strong feelings, they may also cross into unhealthy territory. If you feel uncomfortable or pressured, it\u2019s important to communicate openly about your boundaries. If necessary, don't hesitate to seek support from friends or professionals.",
